d strategies (including <span class=\\"font-weight-bold\\">ownership options<\\/span> and premium structures)<\\/li><li>Premium comparisons over the short and longer term<\\/li><li>Provider financial standing<\\/li><li>Possible underwriting outcomes by different providers<\\/li><li>Provider reputation and adviser experiences<\\/li><\\/ul>","notes":""},{"value":"2","question":"Do you identify and evaluate any <span class=\\"font-weight-bold\\">reasonably foreseeable limitations, risks and disadvantages<\\/span> of the products or solutions recommended.","notes":""},{"value":"2","question":"Are notes on your <span class=\\"font-weight-bold\\">rationale<\\/span> leading to the advice (research and analysis outcomes as above) documented and on file?","notes":""},{"value":"2","question":"Are you satisfied any <span class=\\"font-weight-bold\\">product research<\\/span> or analysis not conducted by you can be relied upon and can you demonstrate this?","notes":""},{"value":"2","question":"Do you identify and evaluate areas where the client needs to get <span class=\\"font-weight-bold\\">specialist advice<\\/span> such as a legal, estate planning or accounting","notes":""}],"step4":[{"value":"2","question":"Do you provide a written record or <span class=\\"font-weight-bold\\">Statement of Advice<\\/span> to your clients?","notes":""},{"value":"2","question":"Are recommendations in the Statements of Advice written\\/presented in a <span class=\\"font-weight-bold\\">clear, concise and effective<\\/span> way and suitable to:<ul><li>The level of sophistication of the client?<\\/li><li>Any identified client vulnerabilities?<\\/li><li>The level and nature of the advice as agreed in the Scope of Engagement.<\\/li><\\/ul>","notes":""},{"value":"2","question":"Do you check all advice documents to ensure there are no misleading (or likely to mislead) statements or omission of relevant information?","notes":""},{"value":"2","question":"Do you restate the <span class=\\"font-weight-bold\\">Scope of Service<\\/span> and any other terms of the engagement?","notes":""},{"value":"2","question":"Do you summarise <span class=\\"font-weight-bold\\">key relevant <u>facts<\\/u><\\/span> and <span class=\\"font-weight-bold\\">client circumstances<\\/span> on which your advice is based?","notes":""},{"value":"2","question":"Do you summarise the client\\u2019s core <span class=\\"font-weight-bold\\">needs and objectives<\\/span> (in personal and practical terms) and their priorities?","notes":""},{"value":"2","question":"Does the advice clearly outline any considerations in arriving at your advice? For example:<ul><li>Client\\u2019s risks tolerance\\/capacity<\\/li><li>Priorities<\\/li><li>Choice of product provider<\\/li><li>Known limitations to the advice e.g. needs identified but unable to address, insufficient information provided<\\/li><li>Reasons for cancelling or retaining existing cover<\\/li><li>Any restrictions to being able to provide best possible solution e.g. health status of client and any alternative risk management strategies<\\/li><li>Government support available and their impact<\\/li><li>Tax implications<\\/li><\\/ul>","notes":""},{"value":"2","question":"Does your advice clearly define the underpinning strategies recommended to address client\\u2019s needs and objectives?","notes":""},{"value":"2","question":"Does the advice clearly state how your product recommendations will meet the needs, circumstances and objectives of the client? This may include:<ul><li>Cover types and benefit structures<\\/li><li>Sums insured<\\/li><li>Premium type(s)<\\/li><li>Optional Options recommended<\\/li><li>Ownership structures recommended etc<\\/li><\\/ul>","notes":""},{"value":"2","question":"Is the advice presented based on identified needs <u>and not modified<\\/u> to represent the client\\u2019s final decision e.g. Accepting only part of the recommendation?","notes":""},{"value":"2","question":"Does the advice clearly state any identified risks, limitations or disadvantages of the recommended strategies or product solutions? For example:<ul><li>Needs identified but not addressed<\\/li><li>Replacement of policy and possible risks and consequences of non-disclosure<\\/li><li>Insufficient provision of information<\\/li><li>Not implementing the recommendations<\\/li><\\/ul>","notes":""},{"value":"2","question":"Does the recommendation clearly outline the premium costs (or your fees) of implementing the recommended strategies and products?","notes":""},{"value":"2","question":"Do you clearly and effectively communicate any conflicts of interest that might influence your advice<br>e.g. qualification for higher commission<span class=\\"font-weight-bold\\">s or<\\/span> qualifications for overseas trips and other incentives?","notes":""},{"value":"2","question":"Is the need for the client to seek other legal or <span class=\\"font-weight-bold\\">specialist advice<\\/span> identified and noted in your advice? For example: need for Wills, EPAs etc.","notes":""},{"value":"2","question":"Can you evidence you meet all applicable Disclosure Regulations required at this point of the process?","notes":""}],"step5":[{"value":"2","question":"Is there an appropriate place recording any client- initiated variations to the advice?","notes":""},{"value":"2","question":"Do you explain the process of implementation of any strategies and insurance solutions including possible time frames and impact of other requirements such as medical examinations, use of other professionals etc?","notes":""},{"value":"2","question":"Do you discuss the reasons for a review of their plans and products? Is such a <u>review<\\/u> and an appropriate time frame and method recommended and agreed by the client?","notes":""},{"value":"2","question":"Does the client sign an Authority to Proceed? For example:<ul><li>Proceed with full recommendations<\\/li><li>Proceed with noted variations<\\/li><li>Do not proceed with recommendations<\\/li><\\/ul>","notes":""},{"value":"2","question":"Do you carefully support the client through the application questions to ensure they fully understand the disclosure requirements and complete all necessary documentation?","notes":""},{"value":"2","question":"Do you send a copy of their application(s) and reminding them of their Duty of Disclosure? This letter could include:<ul><li>Matters they may have overlooked<\\/li><li>Health\\/Occupation changes since application<\\/li><\\/ul>","notes":""},{"value":"2","question":"Do you monitor and maintain tracking records (file notes) of the application and implementation process to ensure it is keeping within agreed time frames and to keep the client informed?  For example:<ul><li>Discussion with underwriters \\/ new business staff<\\/li><li>Follow up conversations and actions on outstanding requirements<\\/li><li>Discussion of variation to terms of cover and acceptance or otherwise<\\/li><\\/ul>","notes":""}],"step6":[{"value":"2","question":"Can you evidence how you communicate with clients to determine if circumstances and needs have changed (triggers) and\\/or communicated with client and arranged a review","notes":""},{"value":"2","question":"Can you evidence you meet all applicable Disclosure Regulations required at this point of the process?","notes":""},{"value":"2","question":"Conducted a check with the client to understand and identify changes in circumstances and \\/or needs that will necessitate strategy or insurance product changes. Changes may include (but not limited to) such things as:<ul><li>Relationship status<\\/li><li>Family status and responsibilities<\\/li><li>Employment<\\/li><li>Nature and source of income<\\/li><li>Other financial circumstances including assets and liabilities<\\/li><li>Insurances in place (acquired or ended\\/cancelled)<\\/li><li>Risk tolerances and objectives<\\/li><li>Health<\\/li><li>Pastimes and habits<\\/li><li>Goals and aspirations<\\/li><li>Beneficiaries<\\/li><\\/ul>","notes":""}]}', NULL, 'd9bc9b61f5532fa68a08ca839e916cf9', 'Based on percentage'),
